==Winners==
[[File:DeanSmithcropped.jpg|thumb|alt=An older Caucasian man with white hair is standing up on a basketball court. He is wearing navy blue dress pants, a baby blue suit jacket with a white cross-hatching pattern, and a bright yellow tie.|upright|150px|[[Dean Smith]] holds the record for most ACC Coach of the Year Awards with eight.]]
[[File:Bobby Cremins.jpg|thumb|alt=An older, tan Caucasian man with white hair is sitting down on a chair behind a table while speaking to someone off camera. He is wearing a short-sleeved dark blue polo shirt and a gold and silver watch on his left wrist.|upright|150px|[[Bobby Cremins]] won the award three times as the head coach of [[Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets men's basketball|Georgia Tech]].]]
[[File:Dave Odom.jpg|thumb|alt=An older Caucasian man wearing a dirty green baseball cap and white polo shirt is sitting down on a chair in the middle of a basketball court. He is looking off to the left while conversing with a person off-camera.|upright|150px|Between 1991 and 1995, [[Dave Odom]] of [[Wake Forest Demon Deacons men's basketball|Wake Forest]] was named the Coach of the Year on three occasions.]]
[[File:Mike Krzyzewski - basketball coach.jpg|thumb|alt=A head shot of a middle-aged Caucasian man with dark black hair is smiling. He is wearing a dark gray suit with a white undershirt and a blue tie.|upright|150px|[[Duke Blue Devils men's basketball|Duke]]'s current head coach, [[Mike Krzyzewski]], is second all-time in ACC Coach of the Year Awards with five.]]
[[File:GT Hewitt.jpg|thumb|alt=A light-skinned, middle-aged African American man is standing on the sidelines of a basketball game with his arms folded while watching his team. He is wearing a gold tie and white undershirt beneath a deep blue suit that has white vertical pin-stripes.|upright|150px|[[Paul Hewitt]] won the award in 2000<U+2013>01 despite finishing 5th in the ACC.]]
