==Footnotes==
*{{note label|Note 1|a|a}}The 1972<U+2013>73 N.C. State Wolfpack team was forced to skip postseason play due to an NCAA recruiting infraction.<ref name=NCSTATE>{{cite web |last=Crawford| first=Jacob|title =Complete History of NC State Basketball |publisher = NorthCarolinaState.scout.com|date = 26 December 2003|url =http://northcarolinastate.scout.com/2/209048.html |accessdate = 10 March 2010}}</ref> Assistant coach [[Eddie Biedenbach]] had played in a pick-up basketball game with [[David Thompson (basketball)|David Thompson]] on a recruiting visit to [[Raleigh, North Carolina]].<ref name=NCSTATE/> The Wolfpack would finish the season undefeated at 27<U+2013>0 but were never given the opportunity to compete for the national championship.
*{{note label|Note 2|b|b}}The [[University of South Carolina]] left the Atlantic Coast Conference in 1971, and it is now a member of the [[Southeastern Conference]].<ref name=MEMBERS/>

